caption: If you like soup. That's where you go.
Lobster bisque with the sourdough was really good. Definitely going back to try the other soups.
found my new favorite lunch spot
Too slow at night.
Love their soups! The best in chi-town!
Great soups very tasty but, bit expensive. Probably due to the high rents in the area.
Best place for soup the lobster bisque is my favorite
Great staff and selection of food! Great food, especially on those cold days!
I would never think to order soup but am pleased every single time. I love this place!
The best soup. The nicest people. If you went to Indiana University this is like Darn Good’s cousin ❤️
It feels so good to step in when it's chilly outside. They have may soup options, as well as grilled cheese. Tomato-basil is really good. I also love chicken rice and beans soups.

I've always liked Soupbox and have been here many times over the past 8 years. Yesterday, I ordered their lobster bisque, which I already like, but that order was packed with lobster and it was FANTASTIC. I always thought it was maybe a little on the light side lobster wise before, but yesterday's soup was particularly delicious and I just wanted to say thanks! Great business.
Homestyle soup that feels like a warm hug and tastes like mom used to make. Love this place and highly recommend them!
I've been ordering soup box for a while and their food is pretty good. The 2$ loaf of bread is a really good deal and worth stopping by just for that sometimes. It do be warm soup too
Great soup, perfect serving size.
Soup and bread were very good, but it was pretty pricy. I’d have liked to get a bit more soup in the large for the price.

I was recommended Soupbox on the local FB page and it did not disappoint! I was craving chicken noodle soup and it was SO good. Their bread bowls are phenomenal as well! Love supporting a small business during this time and the variety of soups makes it easy :) thanks!
Perfect for a winter day! Soup was  flavorful and they give a lot. Loaf of sourdough only 2$! Definitely will be back , staff very friendly
Yum!! Love it.
Broccoli and cheddar is good. The bread tastes a little different though. Definitely better soup then panera
I was feeling sick and was looking for a good, healthy soup, this place definitely met and exceeded my expectatives. Delivered hot and tasted delicious! Would definitely recommend.

Had a lil delivery mixup and the manager, LaDarius, was insanely kind and helpful and prompt in helping to not only make it right, but go above and beyond in the process. A true gift in the customer service world and the food was pretty dang good too!

1-14-2021 We came in the restaurant good vibes and great team work very clean no wait. Happy go Lucky business. This was our first time in here soups were great. We got the wild rice soup and broccoli and cheddar soup. Thank you they All deserve a raise👍👍👍👍👍👍👍
The server was rude. I won't fo back there
I have to give the soup box this rating because the cashier was very rude to my husband, they didn't give us no plastic utensils or napkins. All and all the food was amazing.
I got this delivered and it showed up still super hot and delicious. Would definitely recommend!!
Friendly, helpful, tasty, socially distanced, and masked.

The team on Wednesday morning 12/23 really made my day, and my god the soup in the bread bowl was divine. I got lobster bisque🦞. Plenty of lobster, nice and creamy, and an over all hearty bisque.  This was my first visit, the team walked me through everything with such delight.  I will definitely be back again and again!!!!

I’d give 4.5 starts but half stars aren’t a thing on here. Ordered the veggie soup via doordash. It arrived piping hot and was wrapped in ceran wrap(sp?) to prevent spillage. It could have used less broth and more veggies but was still very tasty! I definitely want to try more of their menu!

I ordered the Chicken noodle soup with add on of shredded chicken because usually their chicken noodle is very watery. When I received the order it didn’t have the add on.  I made the complaint and they refunded the $1 dollar add on. But that’s not the idea. The soup wasn’t really  good without the add on.  Very disappointed ☹️
Completely overpriced for what is offered. It’s equivalent to canned soup but charged at an absurd price.
Very expensive!
The dessert there is Amazing. Generous with the portions. Very fresh and absolutely yummy. Online delivery orders only. Try it asap. The lemon based options are to LIVE for.

Super overpriced. Not sure where they get off charging 10 dollars for a small bowl of soup. Especially when those soups are lacking in substance. The chicken noodle was over salted and had hardly any chicken or any noodles. The vegetable soup was bland, had very little in the way of vegetables, and had a glob of oregano throw on top. Will definitely never order from there again.
Above average soup, kinda pricey to be honest.
Food is good, but the service is not that great.
Delicious, warm, and tasty!  Great service.  Nice variety of soups, too.  Highly Recommend.
Very tasty and wholesome.  Love the soup in a bread bowl - bread was fresh and tasted delicious.  A perfect compliment to the soup.
The soup is overpriced. Go to Mariano's across the street and get better soup for a third of the price. I ordered the hearty vegetable, and when I got home, I found it was only broth.
12 different soups made fresh daily, and the grilled cheese that you can customize is pretty good too

Biggest ripoff in Chicago. Most expensive soup you will ever have. The 'large' is tiny. To top it off, the soup isn't very good. Chicken noodle doesn't really have chicken in it. Lobster bisque has no fresh lobster chunks in it. How has this place survived? Garbage
Great soups and great grilled cheese sandwiches.
Service is so slow.I dont know what they are doing but i wait 20 minute to deserts

I went there with my friends for dinner on weekdays. The soup was really tasty and beef broth made the soup nice aroma in my mouth. We also had steamed meat with wasabi soy sauce. It was tender and I was addicted. Staff were friendly also. Will come back soon.
If I could give them more stars I would. I ordered the beef stew and it is literally liquid comfort.
Ordered on UberEats. Super fast, well-packed, and delicious. Will definitely order again.
Cool spot
Just picked up my soups and want to thank both ladies serving us today. Great food and service.
Great first impression. Delicious soups.  Chicken and noodle had perfect noodle texture and lobster bisque was a creamy delight.
Great food and friendly staff! I love the variety. So happy this place is back after this awful year.

How do four soups come out to $50!?!? Really expensive. Lobster bisque had no lobster in it. New England Clam Chowder tasted like canned soup from a grocery store. And the Tomato basil and broccoli cheddar were okay.  The customer service was subpar. I do not recommend!!!
Great soup and fast delivery :)

Amazing there really is no words to tell how good it is , if you haven't already what are you waiting for , you may not even like soup ?. But you will . Try it and I and I know what you're going to ask ,. What ? just one location.?.
Very disorganized store rude staff
Great soup

The soup broth was good but cost $11.50 for a bowl of chicken noodle soup. For $11.50 for a bowl of soup I expected some fresh chicken  but there was none. Sorry but too expensive for the soup quality.  Great service.
Soup box is absolutely amazing. The soup is fantastic, the sandwiches are great and the service is always perfect. Highly recommend!

I’ve passed Soupbox no less than a hundred times since I’ve lived in the neighborhood and never stopped in. When I caught the flu and soup was all I could keep down, hubby brought me chicken noodle soup from here and it is the best. Their grilled cheeses are delicious as well and the bread is baked fresh. Soupbox is the ultimate comfort food. It doesn’t get better than this!
The mushroom soup is the best and the sandwiches too. You have to wait 15-20 minutes for the sandwich.
Kinda pricey for the amount of soup you get

Great neighborhood gem!  Always a delicious selection of soups, and the staff is helpful, efficient, and happy.  They often recommend unique soup combinations that I wouldn’t have thought of - for example mixing tomato bisque with broccoli and cheddar (great advice, and yum!)
The most only soup I need when I’m under the weather!
Literally the best lobster bisque i’ve ever had. Highly recommend!!
Best soup in the city.
Best soup in Chicago? Best soup in the WORLD!
Fresh soups made hourly. Great selection.
So expensive got the lobster soup no lobster inside of soup at all... the grill cheese didn’t have no taste to it at all. This place is too expensive and not quality food
No lemon lol. But great service and soups amazing. Thank u guys. 😊😊😊😊😊😊🙏🌸🙏🌸🙏

The soup box is really tasty. The staff is usually pretty friendly and willing to let you sample the soups before to help you decide which one you want. It is a little expensive for soup but the soup is really good! Definitely recommend if you love soup!!
Plenty of healthy options to choose from. Like the fact that you can customize your soup with add-ons.
Really good soup!

The soup broth was good but cost $11.50 for a bowl of chicken noodle soup. For $11.50 for a bowl of soup I expected some fresh chicken  but there was none. Sorry but too expensive for the soup quality.  Great service.
Friendly staff, free samples and pretty great soup

Everything here seems to be fresh! You can try different kinds of soups and then get the one you like! Staff are also very helpful. I took a point off since it is a little bit overpriced. Give it a try ...
I absolutely love this place. All fresh made soups, you can try all before you decide which one to get. I am moving back to this neighborhood and am so excited to get my Soupbox fix!!!!
Asked for a lobster bisque with extra lobster and got literally zero prices of lobster in the entire bread bowl. Full disclosure, This place has been decent in the past.
Yummy beef stew.
The soup is violently moderate and way overpriced, two cups of soup and drinks cost $36! For soup? Idk about anyone else but near $40 for a 12 ounce soup is not ok

This place gets lots of praise, but I came in here tonight with a friend and two bowls of soup were $38.00.  Really.  Thirty eight bucks for two bowls of soup.  I'd look around.  There are better soups and better soup deals out there.
12 different soup options every day the concept is simple, I left her warmed and full from the 16oz chicken soup, amazing!
Best soup. Little pricey but soooooo worth it
Superb customer service! Amazing ans Delicious options of soups! Love my soup in a bread bowl. I had both sour dough and 2nd visit the wheat grain bowl and both are highly recommended!
It tasted like campbells chicken noodle soup. Next to no chicken in the soup. Flavorless,expensive, and a waste of time. Seriously its gross,like honestly disgusting.
Hearty, fresh tasting soup!

12 different types of soup. Always perfect for those cold days or night. When you want something to warm you up. If you love soup then you love definitely love this place. The classic chicken noodle, lobster bisque, broccoli cheddar cheese, & the creamy cheddar potato soup are some of my personal favorites.
The servings are plenty and the toppings for you sandwich are great options, had the grilled cheese with jalapenos and tomatoe soup
Very tasty soups and conveniently located close to the Chicago redline station. The prices are a bit high, but the soups are worth it.
This place is fantastic. Service was excellent and the food even better! Will definitely be back... I recommend the lobster bisque
Soup was amazing. Staff was very friendly and helpful. So many choices.
Super Delicious soups ! Loved it !! 😀😀😀

This place is awesome for soup lovers. Every day there are 12 different soups available. The staff was friendly and offered me the chance to try the soups before buying. Only downside for me is the price. If you like soup, definitely give them a try.

Great options! Nice friendly workers. Comfy chairs
Delicious chicken and wild rice soup 😃
Yummy soups  :)

Where do I start?? I’ve never been to Soup Box before, so upon walking in the door the staff was not very welcoming. While I was trying to decide from the variety of soups, the woman waiting to take my order just stood there and stared she never once said hello or suggested a soup. The man that packed my soup called me ma’am and I’m not a ma’am nor do I look like a ma’am. Now, let’s talk about the soup!! The soup was flavorless and expensive. I could have drunk a cup of hot water for free!! The vegetables in the soup had the consistency of gum. If you want good quality soup at a good price just go across the way to Mariano’s!!

What can I say? Soupbox is always a good option. I haven't had one sip of theirs over the many years that I've been going there that I didn't like. It's not fancy but it's always delicious.
Awesome

Yummmy
yes! i love this place!
Amazing as always. First time going to this one. Always used to go to the one on Chicago ave. Very nice staff.

When they placed my temporary teeth no one told me I might starve to death. The side effects of dental care.  The soup box is the first real meal I could swallow. I can't afford it everyday unless I have it in three sittings but it is so good. I am so happy they offer so many choices. I may not starve after all.  No. Shelf soups suck. Yes. very highly priced.  Marianos up the street may not have the extensive variety of the soup box, but what they offer in soups is first class and much less in cost

The BEST spot for soup! With about 12-15 different kinds of soup and their is a good variety of stores to explore in the area. I've been coming here since Icy-fruit days when I was a KID. I love it.
One of my favorite restaurants, sad the one on the near north side closed. There lobster bisque sourdough bread bowl is the bomb!
Awesome place.
Glad I finally made it in here! The soup was delicous (lobster bisque), and the bread and potato bowl options are fun alternatives. They have grilled cheeses now too, but can't vouch for those...yet!

Stumbled upon this place and so happy I did!!! Love the plant based options they offer!!! The environment was very friendly and clean, and the staff was truly over the top! Can’t wait to return in the future!!

Very fun place! Good staff, they worked with our certificate even though we didn't meet all the requirements! Amazing!!  Great food.  Loved it!

Love this place! The best soup is the lobser bisque. It's so dilic

The Lobster Bisque is their specialty (among others) and delivers the perfect quenching you're looking for on a cold or sick day.
Very friendly staff! I always loved the soup, and they seem to be so positive. It's so infectious!

I had three people ask for my order and then I had to tell the clerk again what I ordered. Not in a rush to come back.

Soup is delicious! Come in with low expectations for this location.. Employees are pretty dirty. Not everyone uses gloves when handling food. Our cashier with bloodshot eyes used bare hands to serve soup and dropped it into the vat, then scooped it out and poured us another one. Afterwards checked us out at the register, does he wash his hands ever during his shift? If they could keep up with the service and cleanliness of the other location on Chicago I'd come back again!
Good selection of soups and small seating area.

While the soup and grilled cheese were very good, the service was anything but. We had the cream of potato and leak, broccoli and cheese and minestrone soups, which were piping hot and very well seasoned. The grilled cheese were nicely done in the press, and complemented the soups well. The variety of soups and sandwiches makes this a place that has something for everyone. However, I shouldn't have to feel as though I'm inconveniencing them with my business, and this is not the first time I've had lackluster service. It was rude, and as a result I can't say that I enjoyed my experience, despite the good food. Given we are talking about soup and sandwiches here, for me there are better alternatives.
Great place first time here. Great people too :]
Everything is delicious. Literally everything.

Their soup is phenomenal can't complain about any of them very fresh and full of flavor. I love chicken noodle but alot of times places will make it a little sweet for my taste but soup box makes it with best combination of flavors. My only knock on the place is the prices me and my wife and two large soups and drinks and it cost nearly 30 dollars that's ridiculous in my opinion.
Heart-shaped grilled cheese. Nuff said.
The sourdough bread is delicious. Soup vegetables were under cooked and do not get the extras it's a waste of money. Tiny portions for the extras. Had better soup at safeway.
Delicious!
They have the best soups!

We needed to find easy, decent food at an decent price and soupbox came to our rescue, they allow you to test out the soups to see if you like them and their grilled cheese IS AMAZING! Coming again soon!
Delicious soup and vast selection but staff made me feel unwelcome. Overpriced for soup so value isn't the best. Location has a lot of hype.
The windows are always foggy, but the food is great.
They ran out of the lobster bisque I wanted to try. The broccoli cheddar soup was ok....
The soups are good, but I think way overpriced. I love soups, but surely for cooking all of it in bulk, the prices can be more reasonable?
Pretty good soup. Just a bit pricey
Great soup but service is always horrible. More than once they've forgotten part of the order.
Good selection of soup. Great for winter
Nice staff, and convenient location

The chicken and rice soup is absolutely amazing - especially on those cold and rainy Chicago days. Plus, you can order a grilled cheese sandwich to accompany it. This place really can't be beat when it comes to soup.

Good selection of soups. They have 12 soups everyday where most of them are available daily and the rest change from day to day. Friendly staff the place is clean. It's a bit pricey though for soup, that's why I gave them 4 stars.
Mmmm mmm Mmmm what a great discovery. ... especially on a cold, rainy December day.
Soup was good but we waited 2 hours for our delivery.  Tried it again 3 weeks later and the same thing happened but they always say it will be 45 min.  Not worth the wait.

Soupbox is part of my “Chicago Winter Survival Plan”. Right off the Magnificent Mile, Soupbox is the perfect place to retreat from the cold and indulge in comfort food. Soupbox soup has an incredible, rich flavor that I’ve never experienced anywhere else. I appreciate the rotating menu of soup and the option to creatively mix two kinds of soup together. I recommend the potato and leek and broccoli and cheddar. Their bread bowls are to die for, and they’ve always got a good playlist going overhead.
An awesome place in cold/rainy months weigh is a substantial part of the year. The process are a touch high but you will be hard pressed to find a better quality soup
Best soup
Best atmosphere and people, not to mention an amazing selection of great soups! Plus, who doesn't want the grilled cheese option with soup? I am coming back for sure!

This place is amazing. Whenever I am sick, I will go out of my way to stop by Soupbox.  The space is fairly small, but they always have at least 10 different soups available, either on their own or in a bread bowl. The chicken and rice is my main go to and is truly some of the best soup I have ever had. They will let you sample as many as you like before you make up your mind. If they opened one closer to me I would go all the time! (hint hint)

This is the best place in the city to get fast food soup. They offer about 12 every day, and the menu varies. I've tried most of them, and haven't been disappointed yet. The beef stew is especially good in a bread bowl, and is often a meal in itself.

Regardless if it is freezing or hot as black leather seats in the sun, this place has awesome soup.  I have tried the lobster bisque and the cream of wild chicken w/ rice and they are fantastic. Well worth the drive.
When I want a hot soup I always go here I love the lobster bisque, my daughter got me hooked..

When you live in Chicago sometimes you just want a nice bowl of hot soup to battle the cold winters. While I do tend to enjoy Asian soups more (especially when I'm sick), when I'm in the neighborhood nothing beats their creamy chicken with wild rice soup. Service is usually fast and I enjoy being able to sample any new soups that are offered that day.
Super nice staff and very accommodating if you're in a bind (Ordered from the wrong location and they forwarded my order correctly to the Chicago Ave. store). I'll definitely be coming back!

This place was good for a quick stop. I ordered 2 paninis and 2 cups of soup. The clam chowder was great but the lobster soup was too buttery and simply didnt tastr good. I think we ended up paying around $23 total which can be expected in the city. Try it out but I wouldnt make it a regular joint I visit.
